# vim:set syntax=kconfig:
config CONFIG_HDPARM
  bool "hdparm - Utility for manipulating Linux IDE drive/driver parameters"
  default n
  help
    hdparm is a Linux shell utility for viewing and manipulating various IDE
    drive and driver parameters. Most drives can benefit from improved
    performance using a command similar to
      
      "hdparm -qm8 -qu1 -qc1 -qd1 /dev/hda".

    http://sourceforge.net/projects/hdparm/
